  "original_title": "Sri Lanka bond yields flat, kerb rate down",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka bond yields flat, kerb rate down",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka Treasury Bills rates and T- bonds rates were steady in active trade on Friday while the Central Bank\u2019s guidance peg for interbank transactions weakened by 40 cents, dealers said.",
        "The kerb rate for the US dollar was 368.00/366.50 rupees and the Euro was at 368/364.50, market participants said.",
        "A bond maturing on 01. 06. 2025 closed at 28.95/29.00 percent of Friday, steady from 28.90/29.05 percent.",
        "Three months\u2019 bill was closed at 30.00/30 percent on Friday unchanged from the Thursday\u2019s close.",
        "Sri Lanka\u2019s central bank announced a guidance peg for interbank transactions weakened by 40 cents to 361.40 rupees against the US dollar on Friday from 361 rupees.",
        "Data showed that commercial banks offered dollars for telegraphic transfers between 368.40 and 370.00 for small transactions.",
        "Banks offered to buy inward remittances at 358.40 -359.00 rupees. (Colombo/ Aug 26/2022)"
      ],
